This is the first of the two courses meant for the first-year MA students at the Department of English Studies which deal with the issues of writing research papers in Anglo-American linguistics, cultures of English-speaking countries, literatures written in English and teaching English as a foreign language. The course focuses on critical reading of academic texts, locating and assessing sources and integrating them into own writing. Students write a critique of a research article and of an MA thesis and compile an annotated bibliography consisting of at least 15 publications in their field of interest.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at supporting MA students at the Department of English Studies in the early stages of their work on their MA theses by providing them with the skills needed for critically reading, analysing and writing research papers in English.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course, students will have the necessary knowledge and skills to - find and critically evaluate sources (including Internet sources) and integrate them into your own writing; - write summaries of different types; - analyse and critically evaluate research articles and theses and write reviews of such papers; - compile annotated bibliographies; - provide constructive feedback on their peers' writing; - critically evaluate and edit their own writing; - use digital resources when writing and editing their own texts.
